    <p>PROMOTIONS</p>
    <p>Se7enth’s Re­freshed Menus</p>
    <p>De­signed by act­ing ex­ec­u­tive chef Gary Lim, the a la carte menu of­fers Western and Eastern dishes. Western high­lights in­clude Alaskan King Crab Seafood Plat­ter With Truf­fle Risotto ($42), Sal­mon En Papil­lote With Wild Mush­room Veloute ($35) and Chicken Roulade With Apri­cot And Raisins ($28). For Asian cui­sine, there is Wagyu Katsu Sand­wich ($35), with breaded medium wagyu striploin steak sand­wiched be­tween grilled brioche; and Oak­wood Premier Nasi Le­mak ($28), which com­prises sam­bal king river prawns, mus­sels, turmeric chicken, fried egg and co­conut milk-in­fused rice. Se7enth has also re­vamped its kids’ menu to of­fer nu­tri­tious choices.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Se7enth, 07-01 OUE Down­town 1, 6 Shen­ton Way</p>
    <p>MRT: Tan­jong Pa­gar WHEN: Lunch: noon - 2pm; din­ner: 6.30 - 10pm</p>
    <p>PRICE: Wagyu Katsu Sand­wich ($35) TEL: 6812-6050 INFO: E-mail se7enth.premier-sin­ga­pore@ oak­wood.com</p>
    <p>White Truf­fles At Zaf­fer­ano</p>
    <p>Till De­cem­ber, savour white truf­fles paired with Zaf­fer­ano’s con­tem­po­rary Ital­ian cui­sine. The sea­sonal spe­cial, house­made tagli­olini pasta ($78++), is served with but­ter sauce and crowned with shav­ings of Alba white truf­fle. Din­ers may also add white truf­fles to any dish at $15++ a gram, such as Ta­jima beef ten­der­loin carpac­cio with Parme­san cheese and 25-year-old bal­samic vine­gar ($26++) and creamy risotto in saf­fron sauce with ram­sons and roasted bone mar­row (from $28++).</p>
    <p>WHERE: Zaf­fer­ano, Level 43 Ocean Fi­nan­cial Cen­tre, 10 Col­lyer Quay</p>
    <p>MRT: Raf­fles Place WHEN: Tue - Fri:11.30am - 3pm, 5.30 - 11.30pm;</p>
    <p>Sat & Sun: 6 - 11.30pm TEL: 6509-1488</p>
    <p>INFO: E-mail info@zaf­fer­ano.sg</p>
    <p>Good­wood Park Ho­tel’s Durian Dessert Buf­fet</p>
    <p>The durian dessert buf­fet ($58.80++ a per­son) at Cof­fee Lounge fea­tures Mao Shan Wang mousse cake, crepe, swiss roll and eclair, as well as D24 treats like D24 durian puff and ice cream (one serv­ing a guest). Top up with any a la carte main at $48.80++ a per­son. A la buf­fets that in­clude the durian dessert buf­fet are: Tai­wan por­ridge a la carte buf­fet ( $72++); a three-course De­sign Your Own Lo­cal De­gus­ta­tion Menu ($62++) and a four-course De­sign Your Own Lo­cal De­gus­ta­tion Menu ($66+).</p>
    <p>WHERE: Cof­fee Lounge, Good­wood Park Ho­tel, 22 Scotts Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Or­chard WHEN: Till Nov 15; lunch: noon - 2.30pm; din­ner: 6 - 10.30pm TEL: 6730-1746 INFO: E-mail cof­fee_lounge@ good­wood­parkho­tel.com</p>
    <p>Vi­enna Af­ter­noon Tea At Raf­fles Ho­tel</p>
    <p>In­dulge in clas­sic Aus­trian treats at the ho­tel’s The Grand Lobby – in­clud­ing Vi­en­nese sand­wiches, lob­ster cros­tini and rich choco­late Sacher cake – paired with Mariage Fr­eres pre­mium tea or the Raf­fles cus­tom-blended cof­fee. Guests can also choose from a cu­rated se­lec­tion of hand­crafted cock­tails from the Writ­ers Bar, in­clud­ing Eigh­teen Sixty Seven ($25++), a re­fresh­ing drink of cham­pagne, el­der­flower, saf­fron and eau de vie. Reser­va­tions must be made a day in ad­vance.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Grand Lobby, Raf­fles Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore, 1 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT: City Hall WHEN: Mon - Thu:</p>
    <p>1 - 5pm, Fri - Sun: noon - 6pm, cock­tails are served from 5pm daily PRICE: $78++ a guest</p>
    <p>INFO: str.sg/J6XE</p>
    <p>Re­branded En Din­ing Opens At Cap­i­tal Tower</p>
    <p>En Din­ing, for­merly En Sak­aba, of­fers a buf­fet with its pop­u­lar a la carte items. High­lights in­clude Shabu Shabu hot­pot with a choice of Iberico pork belly (100g), pre­mium beef (100g) and as­sorted veg­eta­bles; and sig­na­ture Ok­i­nawan fare like beef truf­fle carpac­cio – thinly sliced sir­loin driz­zled with cit­rus soya sauce.</p>
    <p>The buf­fet is avail­able for din­ner from Mon­day to Satur­day, and lunch on Satur­day.</p>
    <p>WHERE: En Din­ing, 01-10 Cap­i­tal Tower, 168 Robin­son Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Tan­jong Pa­gar WHEN: Mon - Sat: 11am - 10pm, Din­ner buf­fet: Mon - Sat: 5.30 - 10pm, Sat lunch buf­fet: 11am - 3pm, closed on Sun & pub­lic hol­i­days PRICE: $58++ an adult, $28++ a child aged five - 10, free for child younger than five TEL: 6423-0110</p>
    <p>INFO: www.face­book.com/ EnDin­ingSG</p>
    <p>Mitzo’s Fes­tive Set Menu</p>
    <p>Avail­able only for take­away and de­liv­ery as Mitzo Restau­rant and</p>
    <p>Bar has yet to re­open, the lav­ish six-course meal in­cludes dishes such as the sig­na­ture Spe­cial Bar­be­cued Pork, Deep-Fried Prawns With Fer­mented Bean­curd May­on­naise, Braised Miso Lamb Shank, Chilean Sea Bass With Wild Mush­room Sauce and Unagi And Seaweed Fried Rice.</p>
    <p>The bar has also cre­ated an exclusive cock­tail called Purp Me Up (Os­man­thus Sen­cha-in­fused vodka, St Ger­main, laven­der bit­ters, pome­gran­ate juice, rose ap­ple syrup, ginger ale), which din­ers can in­clude in the set menu. The drink is also avail­able from $15+ a serv­ing.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Mitzo Restau­rant & Bar,</p>
    <p>Level 4 Grand Park Or­chard,</p>
    <p>270 Or­chard Road MRT: Som­er­set WHEN: Nov 1 - Jan 1 PRICE: $148+ (with­out cock­tail), $178+ (with two serv­ings of Purp Me Up)</p>
    <p>TEL: 6603-8855</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/MITZOFEST</p>


